1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:01,970
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,810
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:06,380
(Episode 36)

4
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:07,450
In Ok.

5
00:00:12,020 --> 00:00:13,020
I...

6
00:00:14,490 --> 00:00:15,820
was wrong.

7
00:00:20,860 --> 00:00:21,860
I'm so...

8
00:00:24,260 --> 00:00:25,500
sorry.

9
00:00:46,220 --> 00:00:47,620
Ma'am!

10
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:54,460
Code Blue, Intensive Care Unit.

11
00:00:55,730 --> 00:00:59,760
Code Blue, Intensive Care Unit.

12
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:05,240
Mom.

13
00:01:13,510 --> 00:01:15,550
(Taehan)

14
00:01:15,610 --> 00:01:19,350
For this styling class,
let's do a small, private event.

15
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:21,490
Yes, that's a good way
to increase customer engagement,

16
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:24,290
and it will also help us build
on our premium brand image.

17
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,660
I think it's a great idea.

18
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:29,830
All right. I'll draw up a proposal
based on that direction.

19
00:01:29,890 --> 00:01:30,900
Okay.

20
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:37,740
- Eun Bin.
- Hyun Bin, they found Grandma.

21
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:39,800
What? Where is she?

22
00:01:42,170 --> 00:01:44,810
Okay, I'm on my way.
Text me the address.

23
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:49,250
Ms. Gong. They found my grandmother.

24
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:53,420
- What?
- She's critical. I'm on my way.

25
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,290
You should call home right away too,
Ms. Gong.

26
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:00,120
Hey, call them. Quick.

27
00:02:00,390 --> 00:02:02,390
They might've found your grandpa,
too, you know.

28
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:09,570
Mom, any news?
Did they find Grandpa?

29
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,470
No, they haven't found Grandfather.

30
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,040
But I heard they found
Director Yang's grandmother.

31
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:19,580
Yes. She was by herself.

32
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,950
By herself?
You mean they weren't together?

33
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:27,650
It seems she didn't run away
with Grandfather after all.

34
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:29,020
What?

35
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:32,160
Wait, what are you talking about?

36
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:34,590
It means exactly
what it sounds like.

37
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:38,830
I think we've had it all wrong
for the past 30 years.

38
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:40,900
That's ridiculous.

39
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:49,240
What's going on?
Was the director's grandma alone?

40
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:51,840
Yes.

41
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:55,450
Why? I thought they eloped.

42
00:02:56,010 --> 00:02:57,280
Did they have a fight or something?

43
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,080
Did they break up?

44
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:02,490
She said we've had it wrong
from the very beginning.

45
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:06,160
- Seriously?
- Yes.

46
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:08,290
Hey, I've got to go.

47
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:09,830
Right.

48
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:16,230
What a bombshell.

49
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,500
So you're saying from the start,
the two families...

50
00:03:19,570 --> 00:03:21,570
had no reason to be enemies?

51
00:03:21,870 --> 00:03:25,210
I know, right?
Isn't this a crazy plot twist?

52
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:28,110
But how could they have gotten it
so wrong?

53
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,780
I'm sure they had their reasons.

54
00:03:34,450 --> 00:03:36,650
Anyway, this is great news for us,
right?

55
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:40,560
The obstacle between Pacu Nacho
and Ms. Gong has disappeared.

56
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:43,960
If they weren't enemies at first,
why would they break up, right?

57
00:03:44,230 --> 00:03:45,930
Vice President...

58
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:49,200
But Director Yang's grandmother
is in critical condition.

59
00:03:49,670 --> 00:03:51,400
So don't you think
you're being a little too upbeat?

60
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,340
I must be out of my mind.

61
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:56,340
Sorry.

62
00:03:57,640 --> 00:04:01,050
I wonder why they heard from her
when she was on her deathbed.

63
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:03,950
Good question.

64
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:10,020
Mom...

65
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:15,130
(Intensive Care Unit)

66
00:04:15,830 --> 00:04:16,860
Hyun Bin.

67
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,730
How is my grandmother?

68
00:04:20,630 --> 00:04:21,930
She passed away.

69
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,780
This is all your fault.

70
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,950
It's Father's fault,
and it's my fault.

71
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,690
- What did Mom ever do wrong?
- Mom, please go.

72
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:47,760
My poor mom. What am I going to do?

73
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:49,960
What do I do?

74
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:53,300
- Poor Mom. What am I going to do?
- Dong Suk.

75
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:55,300
Dong Suk.

76
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:00,470
My poor, poor mother.

77
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:03,680
Mom.

78
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,540
Mom.

79
00:05:07,210 --> 00:05:08,210
Grandfather!

80
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:13,250
My poor mom. I can't bear it.

81
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,220
Good grief.

82
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:21,730
All right, I get it.

83
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:27,900
Apparently, she just passed away.

84
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,340
But Mom,

85
00:05:34,170 --> 00:05:37,810
if Eun Bin's grandma
didn't leave with Grandfather,

86
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,380
then why didn't she come home
for 30 years?

87
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:42,510
About that...

88
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:47,150
It seems something terrible happened
to her in the village.

89
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:49,050
Something terrible?

90
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,320
Don't tell me...

91
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:55,760
And Mr. Yang and the family...

92
00:05:56,830 --> 00:06:00,130
apparently misunderstood and thought
she was having an affair.

93
00:06:06,670 --> 00:06:08,070
That's ridiculous.

94
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:14,110
So it was Grandfather's
and Dad's fault.

95
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:17,820
You said Grandfather hit her,
didn't you, Hyun Bin?

96
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:22,620
They ganged up on her and hit her
without hearing her side, right?

97
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:23,820
Eun Bin.

98
00:06:24,490 --> 00:06:28,030
If your folks said you were cheating
and even beat you,

99
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:29,560
I'd run away from home too.

100
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,700
But how could she stay away
for 30 years?

101
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,470
Poor Grandma.

102
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:38,770
She was just the victim here.

103
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:43,640
She should have told the truth,
whatever her family thought.

104
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,910
Seriously.

105
00:06:48,410 --> 00:06:50,950
People thought differently
back then.

106
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:55,690
When victims spoke out,
instead of family support,

107
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,220
victim-blaming was rampant.

108
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:02,190
She must have been afraid
they wouldn't understand.

109
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:04,760
I know, but still...

110
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:08,470
It's so heartbreaking.
She must have felt terribly wronged.

111
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:13,440
She must have blamed herself,
thinking it was her own fault.

112
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:17,210
Rather than face the blame
from her family or the public,

113
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:20,910
she must've decided to bear the load
all by herself.

114
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:33,360
(Gu In Ok)

115
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,740
(Funeral Condolence Etiquette)

116
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:55,410
(May They Rest in Peace)

117
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,090
The memorial is ready.

118
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:05,120
Let's go in, Father.

119
00:08:06,220 --> 00:08:07,230
I...

120
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:10,390
I killed my mother.

121
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,460
Don't say that.

122
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:17,100
She came back after going through
that horrific ordeal...

123
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:23,540
and I suspected her of infidelity,
shamed her, and hated her.

124
00:08:24,780 --> 00:08:26,740
You didn't know the whole story.

125
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,410
Instead of protecting her...

126
00:08:30,050 --> 00:08:31,420
Instead of keeping her safe...

127
00:08:34,490 --> 00:08:35,490
Hyun Bin.

128
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,590
I was the same with your mother.

129
00:08:39,590 --> 00:08:41,090
And to Se Ri.

130
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:43,490
To both of you.

131
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:46,660
I've always been like this. Always.

132
00:08:47,570 --> 00:08:49,870
I never even bothered
to properly hear anyone out.

133
00:08:50,370 --> 00:08:53,200
I just jump to my own conclusions,
judge them, and hurt them.

134
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,810
The look on my mother's face
the day she left...

135
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:58,480
I can't stop seeing it.

136
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:01,580
How unfairly treated,

137
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,650
and how hopeless?

138
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:24,240
In Ok...

139
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,470
You've gotten so old.

140
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:33,540
We could have grown old together...

141
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:36,580
How did it all come to this?

142
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:41,450
You could have at least told me.

143
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:43,590
For 30 years,

144
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,460
how could you suffer
all by yourself?

145
00:09:48,290 --> 00:09:49,590
Mom...

146
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,600
Mom...

147
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,710
My poor mom...

148
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:12,450
She did nothing wrong, but she lived
all those years like a criminal...

149
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:14,290
and now she's gone.

150
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:17,490
I know.

151
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:21,030
She must have been so scared
and lonely.

152
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,630
It's so unfair to my mom.

153
00:10:25,830 --> 00:10:28,270
My poor mother. It's heartbreaking.

154
00:10:34,610 --> 00:10:37,740
My poor, poor mom.

155
00:10:41,210 --> 00:10:44,320
Grandma must be so conflicted.

156
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,920
Tell me about it.

157
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:49,750
She thought her best friend
betrayed her...

158
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:51,860
and spent 30 years hating her,

159
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:56,030
but finds out she'd been suffering
in hiding all along.

160
00:10:57,430 --> 00:11:01,370
I know.
How did things get so tangled?

161
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:05,140
Shouldn't you be at the funeral?

162
00:11:05,570 --> 00:11:07,810
Oh, that.
I got a text message from work.

163
00:11:07,810 --> 00:11:10,340
It's a private service
so they're not accepting visitors.

164
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:14,650
It must be a difficult time
to receive visitors.

165
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:21,890
A private service means
just relatives are invited, right?

166
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,760
Yes. That's what everyone agreed on.

167
00:11:25,590 --> 00:11:29,060
If other people came
to pay their respects,

168
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:31,930
they'd just ask where Grandma was
and how she lived,

169
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:34,670
and it would just be a series
of awkward questions.

170
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,740
Is there anything we can do
to help, Mom?

171
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:42,640
Could you pick up some toiletries
and towels for the family?

172
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:45,680
Sure, Mom.
Come on, Eun Bin. Let's hurry back.

173
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,960
You should at least have a meal
before you go.

174
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:06,030
No, it's okay. It's private.
We should give you your space.

175
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:08,570
Thank you for coming.

176
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:10,940
Take good care of your family.

177
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:15,470
- I will. Please get home safe.
- Okay. You head on in.

178
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:17,340
- Let's go, Mom.
- Okay.

179
00:12:51,810 --> 00:12:52,880
Min Seo.

180
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:56,610
You've really been through it all
since you came to stay with us.

181
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:58,580
You can say that again.

182
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:03,590
But Eun Bin, your families' story
is so heartbreaking.

183
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:07,490
They spent 30 years as enemies
all because of a misunderstanding.

184
00:13:07,830 --> 00:13:10,230
They were more than just enemies.

185
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:14,370
Always at each other's throats,
ready to tear each other apart.

186
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:19,340
But now that
the misunderstanding's cleared up,

187
00:13:19,770 --> 00:13:23,670
do you think your aunt and his uncle
can get back together?

188
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:28,350
I doubt it's that simple.

189
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:30,780
There's no reason for anyone
to oppose it anymore.

190
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,820
(Message)

191
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:46,900
Ji Hu, could you take
these to your mom?

192
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,200
What's all this?

193
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:54,640
Your mom cried so much,
I was worried she'd get chills,

194
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:58,040
I got her a blanket and hot packs.
And inside,

195
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:01,950
I packed some headache medicine
and other first-aid supplies too.

196
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,250
If your mom feels sick,

197
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,950
make sure
you take care of her, okay?

198
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:06,620
Okay.

199
00:14:07,050 --> 00:14:08,850
Thank you, Mr. Gong.

200
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:11,960
Also, I'm not going home.
I'll be right here.

201
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,920
So if you need anything
or if something comes up,

202
00:14:13,990 --> 00:14:16,090
you have to let me know. Got it?

203
00:14:16,830 --> 00:14:19,930
- I will.
- Okay, go on now.

204
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,500
Grandma...

205
00:14:24,570 --> 00:14:28,110
Woo Jae, get some headache medicine.
Grandma says her head hurts.

206
00:14:28,170 --> 00:14:30,610
- Okay.
- Mother, have you eaten yet?

207
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:32,010
No. I don't have an appetite.

208
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:35,010
- I'm just going to go lie down.
- Yes. Of course, Mom.

209
00:14:50,430 --> 00:14:54,530
You need to eat something.
You'll collapse if you keep this up.

210
00:14:56,700 --> 00:15:00,100
Then go home and get some sleep.
Don't try to sleep here.

211
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,670
There are no other mourners coming.

212
00:15:02,310 --> 00:15:03,770
You don't need to be here.

213
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,980
- Grandfather.
- Leave me be.

214
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,780
I'll just die right here too.

215
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:24,430
Don't just sit there.
Please eat something.

216
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,060
Eat something
to keep your strength up.

217
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,200
Thank you.

218
00:15:28,670 --> 00:15:29,730
There's nothing to thank me for.

219
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:32,100
I'm just doing my part.

220
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,910
Honey, won't you eat with...

221
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:46,080
Was Bucket's wife
at the hospital too?

222
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,520
Of course she was there.

223
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:52,590
That's a relief.
I heard they were separated...

224
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:54,260
Separated?

225
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:56,930
Right, I guess they were
going through some things.

226
00:15:58,430 --> 00:15:59,730
How's Bucket doing?

227
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,200
How do you think he's doing?

228
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:04,670
He's completely devastated.

229
00:16:05,870 --> 00:16:07,000
And what about you?

230
00:16:09,070 --> 00:16:11,710
To be honest,
I'm really confused too.

231
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:15,750
Everything I've known for 30 years
has just been turned upside down.

232
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:18,320
Honey.

233
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:21,690
Do you remember everything
about the day Father disappeared?

234
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:23,750
Yes, of course I remember.

235
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:27,930
He had a patient in Wolseon-dong
who couldn't move after a fall.

236
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,330
He went there to make a house call.

237
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:34,870
Go to the police substation
first thing in the morning.

238
00:16:35,930 --> 00:16:37,870
Your brother called.

239
00:16:38,770 --> 00:16:41,940
We're filing a missing person report
for your father first.

240
00:16:42,810 --> 00:16:45,510
Right, I guess
that is what we have to do.

241
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,050
But didn't your brother
come with you?

242
00:16:56,050 --> 00:16:57,220
Hey, Ji Hu.

243
00:16:57,860 --> 00:16:59,690
What is it? Is something wrong?

244
00:17:00,460 --> 00:17:03,690
No. My mom's exhausted
and finally sleeping,

245
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:07,700
so you don't have to stay.
You should go home.

246
00:17:07,930 --> 00:17:08,930
Right...

247
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:12,200
Okay. I'll get going then.

248
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,170
Get home safe.

249
00:17:15,810 --> 00:17:17,440
Thank you again
for everything today.

250
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:18,740
Sure.

251
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,680
You should go get some sleep
next to your mom, too.

252
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:22,310
Okay.

253
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:25,950
Excuse me, Mr. Gong.

254
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:27,320
What?

255
00:17:27,950 --> 00:17:30,050
My grandma and your father...

256
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:32,020
It turns out
they didn't run away together.

257
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:35,590
Right, that is what it seemed like.

258
00:17:36,390 --> 00:17:38,700
Then that means
if you and my mom get together,

259
00:17:39,230 --> 00:17:40,760
there shouldn't be
any problem, right?

260
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,800
I don't know about that.

261
00:17:44,670 --> 00:17:46,470
Both of our families
are heartbroken,

262
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:49,240
and your mom must be
in shock right now...

263
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:53,510
I have to find my father,
so it's too soon for that, Ji Hu.

264
00:17:54,010 --> 00:17:55,010
So that's all it is, right?

265
00:17:56,180 --> 00:17:57,250
What?

266
00:17:57,580 --> 00:17:58,650
It wasn't because of how...

267
00:17:58,650 --> 00:17:59,850
my grandfather
and uncle acted, was it?

268
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:01,990
You weren't hurt by them?

269
00:18:03,050 --> 00:18:04,120
You haven't...

270
00:18:05,290 --> 00:18:06,960
completely turned your back on us,
have you?

271
00:18:09,260 --> 00:18:10,260
You're something else,
you know that?

272
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,500
Now, go on inside.

273
00:18:17,270 --> 00:18:18,340
We'll talk about this another time.

274
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,400
Okay.

275
00:18:21,140 --> 00:18:22,140
I'm heading in.

276
00:18:35,690 --> 00:18:37,290
How could I have been so stupid...

277
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,390
to believe such a baseless rumor?

278
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:44,900
Anyone would have.
They disappeared on the same day,

279
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:46,760
and there was even a witness.

280
00:18:47,530 --> 00:18:48,570
Then...

281
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:51,140
if he wasn't having an affair,

282
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:54,440
then why didn't he ever come back?

283
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:59,280
Was it some other woman, not In Ok?

284
00:19:00,110 --> 00:19:03,410
I don't think so.

285
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:10,020
To be honest,
I never really believed it anyway.

286
00:19:10,390 --> 00:19:14,860
You and Father used to waltz daily.
You two had a great relationship.

287
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,830
Yes, we did.

288
00:19:18,530 --> 00:19:21,430
Besides, Father was
just like my husband,

289
00:19:21,630 --> 00:19:24,640
he cherished the hospital
and his patients so much.

290
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:29,810
It was strange he would just leave
everything he'd built behind.

291
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,410
You're right.
Now that I think about it,

292
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:36,550
so many things didn't add up.

293
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:39,750
Excuse me, Mother.

294
00:19:40,450 --> 00:19:41,450
Yes?

295
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:46,390
You should cancel your appointment
with the divorce lawyer tomorrow.

296
00:19:49,630 --> 00:19:52,800
Right now, finding Father
should be our top priority.

297
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,700
Okay. You're right.

298
00:19:57,870 --> 00:19:58,870
Okay.

299
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:10,850
Hello?

300
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:18,090
Hey, Eun Bin. Yes, it is me.
Where are you? Are you doing okay?

301
00:20:18,990 --> 00:20:22,060
Hey, could I ask you for a favor?

302
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:24,230
Of course. What is it?

303
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:29,300
- You know where my mom's store is?
- Yes, I do.

304
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:31,100
In that case,

305
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:36,510
could you put up "closed" signs
at my mom's store and my aunt's?

306
00:20:36,810 --> 00:20:41,780
Of course. While I'm at it,
I'll do the Korean clinic too.

307
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:44,010
Thanks so much.

308
00:20:44,450 --> 00:20:45,950
Don't mention it.

309
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:50,050
Eun Bin, is there anything you need?
Should I stop by?

310
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:52,990
Eun Bin?

311
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:03,970
(Notice of Temporary Closure,
Closed for 2 days for a family loss)

312
00:21:09,470 --> 00:21:12,010
Oh, my. Did someone pass away?

313
00:21:12,510 --> 00:21:16,750
We were just asked to put this up.
We don't really know the details.

314
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:18,680
I see.

315
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:23,750
Why did you say you don't know?
It's not like it's a secret.

316
00:21:24,150 --> 00:21:26,560
You should've told her that
Dr. Yang's mother passed away,

317
00:21:26,860 --> 00:21:30,430
and that she and Director Gong
didn't elope 30 years ago.

318
00:21:31,430 --> 00:21:32,700
If I start bringing that up,

319
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:36,000
what do I say when they ask
why she left home to begin with?

320
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:38,300
Oh, for crying out loud.

321
00:21:38,770 --> 00:21:43,210
All that education for nothing.
Just make up an excuse, can't you?

322
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:46,280
Fine. Do whatever you want.

323
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:50,610
Dad and Uncle said they'll stop by
the police substation before work.

324
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:52,520
- I'm leaving.
- Okay, go ahead.

325
00:21:55,890 --> 00:22:01,290
Shall I spread the word around town?
It's been a while.

326
00:22:02,690 --> 00:22:07,160
At 8 p.m., he went to Wolseon-dong
for a patient who had fallen.

327
00:22:07,530 --> 00:22:10,130
When he wasn't back late that night,
I tried calling.

328
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:13,340
But they said he never showed up
at the patient's house.

329
00:22:13,970 --> 00:22:17,840
Were there any signs he was planning
to run away before this?

330
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:20,980
Like packing his things
or making a large withdrawal?

331
00:22:21,410 --> 00:22:24,510
- No, none.
- No. Nothing like that at all.

332
00:22:24,820 --> 00:22:27,850
You mentioned
recent sightings, right?

333
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:30,650
Yes. They both said they saw him
in Seongdam City.

334
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:34,890
They said they saw Father.
One said it was at an eyeglass shop,

335
00:22:35,030 --> 00:22:37,230
and the other at a tailor shop.

336
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:40,700
- Yes, but he wasn't at either one.
- Right.

337
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:42,900
- Jeong Han.
- And also,

338
00:22:43,030 --> 00:22:46,200
- an unknown number just texted him.
- I see.

339
00:22:46,270 --> 00:22:49,970
It said, "I have no plans to return.
Don't look for me again."

340
00:22:51,580 --> 00:22:53,910
Do you have the number?

341
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:57,950
Yes, it's this number right here.

342
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:01,280
The phone's been off ever since.

343
00:23:01,650 --> 00:23:06,160
Once the info is processed, the case
will go to Onjeong Police Station.

344
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:10,960
But our Officer Jeong will keep you
updated on the investigation.

345
00:23:11,130 --> 00:23:12,860
So, please don't worry too much.
Okay?

346
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:16,500
This is a key case for us, right?

347
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,240
- Thank you.
- Of course.

348
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:21,640
- We're really counting on you.
- Yes, right.

349
00:23:21,710 --> 00:23:23,740
Of course.
We'll do our absolute best.

350
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:25,210
Thank you.

351
00:23:26,410 --> 00:23:27,780
- It will turn out fine.
- Yes.

352
00:23:28,910 --> 00:23:32,880
Oh my goodness.
So they didn't elope?

353
00:23:33,020 --> 00:23:36,050
That's what I'm saying.
Someone started a vicious rumor.

354
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:39,920
Then why did
Dr. Yang's wife leave him?

355
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:44,630
From what I hear,
they had a big fight that night.

356
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:48,700
My goodness. She's a piece of work.
To just leave and never come back?

357
00:23:48,770 --> 00:23:52,100
Please. I've wanted to do that too.
Good grief.

358
00:23:52,970 --> 00:23:56,440
I'd love to kick my old man out
and live by myself.

359
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:59,280
Gosh, listen to you,
the things you say.

360
00:23:59,410 --> 00:24:04,080
Quiet! Anyway, it so happened
that Director Gong vanished then,

361
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:06,980
and that's how this absurd rumor
got started.

362
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:08,690
I feel terrible.

363
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:11,760
To think we believed
such a baseless rumor.

364
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:14,960
Exactly.
We have to search for him now.

365
00:24:15,230 --> 00:24:18,600
We waited because of the rumor,
but we'll find him.

366
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:23,500
But after 30 years?
Can you really find him now?

367
00:24:23,570 --> 00:24:26,070
Hey, I'm telling you, we can.

368
00:24:27,070 --> 00:24:29,840
- I'm off.
- Okay, see you.

369
00:24:29,910 --> 00:24:31,980
- Bye.
- We're heading out too.

370
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,480
All right, see you, ladies.

371
00:24:33,540 --> 00:24:35,950
We really misunderstood. I know.
Goodness.

372
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:43,990
- Ms. Na.
- Hey, you are here.

373
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:47,320
Yes. I was at the market shopping
and thought I'd stop by.

374
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:50,360
But what's all this I'm hearing?

375
00:24:50,730 --> 00:24:52,330
I can't believe
it was all just a nasty rumor.

376
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:56,470
What?
Is it all over the market already?

377
00:24:56,630 --> 00:25:00,400
Yes. You know how these women are.
They're going crazy.

378
00:25:02,670 --> 00:25:04,310
That's rumors for you.

379
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:08,410
They get twisted with every telling.

380
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:10,050
Tell me about it.

381
00:25:11,310 --> 00:25:16,450
So who do you think
started such a nasty rumor?

382
00:25:18,020 --> 00:25:19,790
Who knows?

383
00:25:21,660 --> 00:25:24,430
Anyway,
what are you going to do now?

384
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:28,630
The kids reported him missing
to the police.

385
00:25:29,170 --> 00:25:31,230
We've decided to be more proactive
about searching for him.

386
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:33,440
He's not in Seongdam, though.

387
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,370
I'm telling you,
I searched high and low.

388
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:39,480
I know.

389
00:25:39,980 --> 00:25:42,650
I am sorry to have troubled you
for nothing, Mi Hyang.

390
00:25:47,580 --> 00:25:49,820
I'll be praying you find him,
Ms. Na.

391
00:25:51,150 --> 00:25:52,160
Thank you.

392
00:25:56,930 --> 00:25:58,930
For this upcoming styling class,

393
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:02,930
how about we invite back
the VIP clients...

394
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,600
from our One-Point Lesson?

395
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:10,970
Wouldn't that make things awkward
for Ms. Gong?

396
00:26:11,210 --> 00:26:12,610
Director Yang's mother
will be there, after all.

397
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:14,710
Let's keep it professional.

398
00:26:16,410 --> 00:26:19,620
A good chance to fix our image.
It sounds like a great idea.

399
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,990
I assume it would be difficult
for Dr. Han to attend?

400
00:26:23,890 --> 00:26:27,360
She just had surgery,
so I think that would be too much.

401
00:26:27,820 --> 00:26:30,230
How is Dr. Han feeling?

402
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:34,400
We don't have the final results yet.
We'll have to wait and see.

403
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:39,500
Let's pick our presentation looks
and meet back here.

404
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:41,170
- Okay.
- Right.

405
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:47,680
(Executive Director)

406
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:01,960
Hey, about you quitting.
Let's rethink this.

407
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:04,130
I knew you were going to do this.

408
00:27:04,930 --> 00:27:08,230
Let's not fight over who quits.
Let's just both not quit.

409
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:12,840
- Aren't you tired of nagging me?
- Aren't you tired of rejecting me?

410
00:27:12,900 --> 00:27:15,540
I am tired of it.
So please, just stop.

411
00:27:15,610 --> 00:27:18,440
Come on, the family misunderstanding
is cleared up, right?

412
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:19,980
Things are different now.

413
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:21,850
Nothing has changed.

414
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:25,980
What do you mean?
Grandparents never eloped.

415
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:30,490
We didn't break up
because of our grandparents.

416
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:33,890
Then was it because of our mothers?

417
00:27:35,530 --> 00:27:38,090
It was our decision.
We've already decided,

418
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,500
and it's over.

419
00:27:42,170 --> 00:27:43,170
You leave me no choice.

420
00:27:43,570 --> 00:27:46,100
I'll just have to tell Director Yang
not to accept your resignation.

421
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:47,900
Gosh, come on!

422
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:51,540
Director Yang's having a hard time.
Don't you go and make it worse.

423
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:53,180
Gosh, seriously!

424
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:00,820
(May They Rest in Peace)

425
00:28:25,340 --> 00:28:26,380
Hey.

426
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,780
Did you cancel your flight yet?

427
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,350
No, not yet.

428
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:34,350
Don't tell me you're
still thinking about it.

429
00:28:36,490 --> 00:28:39,460
Seriously? When the whole family
is having such a hard time?

430
00:28:39,690 --> 00:28:43,430
I can't believe you.
You're such an ungrateful son.

431
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,400
Fine, go.

432
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:55,170
(Seongsan Jeil Funeral Hall)

433
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,080
Excuse me.

434
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:05,820
You're Laywoman Yeon Sim's
grandson, aren't you?

435
00:29:06,150 --> 00:29:07,180
Yes.

436
00:29:10,490 --> 00:29:11,590
Here.

437
00:29:12,090 --> 00:29:15,590
These are some belongings
from where Laywoman Yeon Sim stayed.

438
00:29:16,030 --> 00:29:18,930
I figured her family
should have them.

439
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:26,140
She was there for 30 years,
but this is...

440
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:27,940
all she had.

441
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:45,120
This...

442
00:29:45,860 --> 00:29:47,590
is Grandma's prayer journal.

443
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:50,630
It looks like she prayed
for our family...

444
00:29:50,890 --> 00:29:53,600
at dawn every single day.

445
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:58,030
You're right.

446
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:01,070
She didn't miss a single day.

447
00:30:01,940 --> 00:30:03,940
She even wrote in it
just a few days ago.

448
00:30:10,850 --> 00:30:11,850
And this...

449
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:16,950
is the stipend she received
for working as a cook at the temple,

450
00:30:18,150 --> 00:30:21,120
and they said she saved it up
little by little.

451
00:30:22,490 --> 00:30:24,990
She said if she saw her children
and grandchildren again,

452
00:30:25,860 --> 00:30:27,600
she wanted to give this to them.

453
00:30:34,570 --> 00:30:35,610
And this one.

454
00:30:37,110 --> 00:30:38,610
A while ago, at the temple,

455
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,480
she participated in an end-of-life
experience program,

456
00:30:42,210 --> 00:30:45,050
and this is apparently the letter
she wrote to her family then.

457
00:31:07,970 --> 00:31:09,040
My gosh.

458
00:31:10,140 --> 00:31:14,040
I can't believe this. Mom.

459
00:31:29,660 --> 00:31:32,560
Who's Na Seon Hae?

460
00:31:35,570 --> 00:31:36,970
There's one for the Ms. Na too.

461
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:40,540
- This one's yours.
- Right.

462
00:31:43,810 --> 00:31:45,170
There isn't one for me.

463
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:48,180
You weren't even born back then.

464
00:31:48,850 --> 00:31:49,850
Right.

465
00:31:52,220 --> 00:31:53,520
What does it say?

466
00:31:54,380 --> 00:31:55,720
She wondered how I've grown up...

467
00:31:58,050 --> 00:31:59,660
and that she missed me so much.

468
00:32:01,260 --> 00:32:02,660
I'm so glad.

469
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:06,160
You said Grandma
saw us all on TV, right?

470
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,940
- Jeong Han.
- Yes?

471
00:32:21,010 --> 00:32:22,980
About tomorrow...

472
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:25,420
What? For the funeral procession?

473
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,550
Yes, I would like to go.

474
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:32,060
I am going too.
Dong Ik has few relatives,

475
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,020
so I should go help
carry the casket.

476
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:38,230
Then could you ask Woo Jae to take
your wife to the hospital tomorrow?

477
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:41,500
Of course, you don't have to ask.
I'll tell Woo Jae to take her.

478
00:32:41,830 --> 00:32:43,170
Great, thanks.

479
00:32:43,530 --> 00:32:44,600
Hey, Dae Han.

480
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:47,270
About the...

481
00:32:48,340 --> 00:32:49,340
What?

482
00:32:50,310 --> 00:32:55,280
How about you delay finding a house
and switching hospitals for a bit?

483
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,780
I was already planning to.

484
00:32:58,310 --> 00:33:00,080
Finding our father is the priority,
after all.

485
00:33:00,450 --> 00:33:03,220
Right, that too, but...

486
00:33:03,950 --> 00:33:04,950
What?

487
00:33:06,320 --> 00:33:08,660
No, it's nothing. Go on. Go inside.

488
00:33:09,030 --> 00:33:10,030
Right.

489
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:12,530
- Thanks.
- Sure.

490
00:33:18,630 --> 00:33:21,140
(Seongsan Jeil Funeral Hall)

491
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:03,350
We're here, sir.

492
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:05,480
You came all this way again?

493
00:34:06,050 --> 00:34:08,650
Yes, we came to see her off...

494
00:34:09,220 --> 00:34:11,120
and pay our final respects.

495
00:34:12,020 --> 00:34:13,160
Thank you.

496
00:34:15,690 --> 00:34:16,690
Here.

497
00:34:17,530 --> 00:34:19,930
- Take it.
- What is this?

498
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:22,130
It's condolence money.

499
00:34:22,370 --> 00:34:24,570
From the Merchants'
Association heads,

500
00:34:24,570 --> 00:34:26,800
the market vendors, and patients.

501
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,770
They couldn't all make it,

502
00:34:30,470 --> 00:34:32,710
but they said they really wanted
to express their sympathies.

503
00:34:33,380 --> 00:34:34,540
Thank you all.

504
00:34:35,180 --> 00:34:37,010
I'll make sure to thank them
personally.

505
00:34:42,620 --> 00:34:44,090
(Onjeong Police Substation)

506
00:34:45,090 --> 00:34:46,160
You startled me.

507
00:34:46,890 --> 00:34:48,420
Where should we go for lunch today?

508
00:34:49,330 --> 00:34:52,960
Actually, I was about to call you.
I don't think I can make it today.

509
00:34:54,060 --> 00:34:55,730
Why not? Are you busy?

510
00:34:56,230 --> 00:34:58,000
There's somewhere I have to be.

511
00:34:58,730 --> 00:35:00,070
Where are you going?

512
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:02,040
I'm going to
the Missing Persons Unit...

513
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:03,840
to speed up the investigation.

514
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:07,080
Why? Are they not making
any progress?

515
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:12,220
They keep giving me the same excuse,
that it's a cold case and not easy.

516
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:15,890
I'll ask them to review the files
and see if they missed anything.

517
00:35:17,820 --> 00:35:19,420
Wow, you're really dedicated.

518
00:35:20,220 --> 00:35:22,760
Of course I have to be.
This is for the manager's family.

519
00:35:23,490 --> 00:35:28,160
Besides, he's the reason
we're together.

520
00:35:30,970 --> 00:35:33,740
Okay. That's a good enough
reason for me.

521
00:35:34,500 --> 00:35:36,610
Go on, then. Go!

522
00:35:37,170 --> 00:35:38,840
Sorry about this. See you later.

523
00:35:47,580 --> 00:35:49,090
Did you lay him to rest properly?

524
00:35:49,550 --> 00:35:53,320
Yes. We laid him to rest
at the columbarium in Danpyeong.

525
00:35:54,490 --> 00:35:57,390
The weather was especially
nice today, too.

526
00:35:57,890 --> 00:35:58,900
Good.

527
00:35:59,830 --> 00:36:00,900
You've all been through so much.

528
00:36:01,930 --> 00:36:04,270
Did the hospital appointment
with Woo Jae go well?

529
00:36:04,730 --> 00:36:06,840
That's right.
Did you get the results?

530
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,000
What did they say?

531
00:36:10,510 --> 00:36:12,880
Hey, what is it? What is wrong?

532
00:36:14,780 --> 00:36:17,210
We haven't decided
about chemotherapy yet.

533
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:20,450
There are also micrometastases
in the lymph nodes,

534
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:23,590
and the tumor activity score
is in a gray area.

535
00:36:24,450 --> 00:36:26,220
So what does that mean?

536
00:36:27,020 --> 00:36:29,890
We registered her
for a genomic analysis test.

537
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:32,560
They said the results will take
about two weeks.

538
00:36:34,260 --> 00:36:38,670
When we get those back, we'll know
the best course of treatment.

539
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:43,270
It's alright.

540
00:36:43,610 --> 00:36:46,280
It's not like I expected
to be cured overnight.

541
00:36:49,910 --> 00:36:52,050
Mother. Dae Han.

542
00:36:52,620 --> 00:36:54,450
This is all part of the process.

543
00:36:55,020 --> 00:36:56,690
Everything that's happening
right now...

544
00:36:56,750 --> 00:37:00,220
is just a step
on our family's path to happiness.

545
00:37:01,020 --> 00:37:04,690
It's hard now, but time will pass,
and this all will too.

546
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:07,760
When we look back on this,
it won't seem like such a big deal.

547
00:37:08,730 --> 00:37:10,500
Okay? Right, everyone?

548
00:37:22,410 --> 00:37:23,410
Father.

549
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,780
You have to stay strong.

550
00:37:28,780 --> 00:37:30,050
Now, more than ever,

551
00:37:31,450 --> 00:37:33,390
I don't see the point
in living anymore.

552
00:37:33,990 --> 00:37:36,260
Don't say that, Father.

553
00:37:37,060 --> 00:37:40,060
You need to get your strength back
and look after us.

554
00:37:44,470 --> 00:37:45,670
Sometimes...

555
00:37:46,470 --> 00:37:47,940
I've wondered about something.

556
00:37:49,670 --> 00:37:51,940
If my parents were still alive,

557
00:37:52,710 --> 00:37:55,140
I wonder what they
would've wanted for me.

558
00:37:57,880 --> 00:37:59,650
Just for me to be healthy,

559
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:02,350
be loved by my family,

560
00:38:03,250 --> 00:38:05,250
and live happily.
I'm sure that's what they'd want.

561
00:38:06,420 --> 00:38:07,790
And I think that's what Mother...

562
00:38:08,390 --> 00:38:10,260
would want the same for you.

563
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:15,430
Stay healthy,
and live a long, long life, Father.

564
00:38:16,100 --> 00:38:18,130
You have to see Hyun Bin
and Eun Bin get married,

565
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:20,300
and meet your great-grandchildren.

566
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,410
I can't lose you, Father.
I just can't.

567
00:38:47,830 --> 00:38:48,830
Hey...

568
00:38:49,930 --> 00:38:52,070
You heard that Hyun Bin
isn't leaving, right?

569
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:53,840
Yes.

570
00:38:55,270 --> 00:38:58,640
So does that mean you'll be
staying here at the house now?

571
00:38:59,410 --> 00:39:02,950
No. Hyun Bin said he'll take care
of Father for a while,

572
00:39:03,550 --> 00:39:06,880
so until Min Seo goes back,
I plan on staying at the apartment.

573
00:39:08,620 --> 00:39:09,620
Right.

574
00:39:10,090 --> 00:39:12,790
I'll make something
for Father to eat before I go,

575
00:39:13,160 --> 00:39:14,220
so please make sure he eats.

576
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:16,830
You don't have to do that.

577
00:39:18,330 --> 00:39:19,930
I need to do my part.

578
00:39:21,060 --> 00:39:25,300
It's easy to get run down now,
so please look after him well.

579
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:28,400
I will.

580
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:51,130
Gosh, you know what?
I think I should just stay home.

581
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:53,330
Mom, come on.

582
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:57,170
I know you're worried,
but please don't, Mom.

583
00:39:57,870 --> 00:40:00,600
If you flake out now,
this was all for nothing.

584
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:03,770
I really don't know
if this is the right thing to do.

585
00:40:04,270 --> 00:40:07,180
It is. How long are you going
to do everything?

586
00:40:07,310 --> 00:40:09,680
Min Seo, don't let Mom leave
the studio apartment.

587
00:40:10,010 --> 00:40:11,450
Okay. See you tomorrow, Eun Bin.

588
00:40:11,910 --> 00:40:15,650
- Girls.
- Mom, I'm all grown up.

589
00:40:16,020 --> 00:40:18,190
If you can't trust me,
then trust Yang Hyun Bin.

590
00:40:18,450 --> 00:40:21,790
Yang Hyun Bin won't go to Argentina.
See? It'll be fine.

591
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:24,590
Gosh, just go already.

592
00:40:28,060 --> 00:40:29,060
Go on, Mom.

593
00:40:38,110 --> 00:40:40,740
I'm sorry for asking you
to come out so late.

594
00:40:41,910 --> 00:40:44,110
You must be exhausted
after the funeral.

595
00:40:44,410 --> 00:40:45,610
What's this about?

596
00:40:46,350 --> 00:40:48,250
How were your test results today?

597
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:50,190
You knew it was today?

598
00:40:51,050 --> 00:40:52,050
Of course.

599
00:40:54,060 --> 00:40:55,420
They're not great.

600
00:40:57,290 --> 00:41:00,330
I'm sure you didn't call me out here
this late just to ask about that.

601
00:41:01,660 --> 00:41:02,730
Actually,

602
00:41:03,570 --> 00:41:05,730
this is a message
for her grandmother,

603
00:41:06,040 --> 00:41:07,600
but she seems to be having
a very hard time.

604
00:41:08,370 --> 00:41:09,810
And I was told...

605
00:41:10,210 --> 00:41:12,340
that you and Ju Ah
tell each other everything.

606
00:41:12,840 --> 00:41:13,840
That's right.

607
00:41:14,710 --> 00:41:17,980
That you and Ju Ah were dating,

608
00:41:18,350 --> 00:41:20,720
that you were going
to leave the company,

609
00:41:21,420 --> 00:41:23,450
and that Ju Ah decided to resign...

610
00:41:24,420 --> 00:41:25,450
I know all about it.

611
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:31,390
I told her grandmother
that I would quit the company...

612
00:41:31,790 --> 00:41:34,130
and leave Korea.

613
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:37,200
But...

614
00:41:37,730 --> 00:41:39,240
Of course, you have to stay.
In Korea.

615
00:41:39,940 --> 00:41:41,170
With your family.

616
00:41:42,610 --> 00:41:45,510
Yes. So could you pass on
a message for me?

617
00:41:45,940 --> 00:41:48,740
Even though I have to stay in Korea
for reasons beyond my control,

618
00:41:49,210 --> 00:41:52,150
tell her not to worry
about me and Ju Ah.

619
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:54,680
Are you sure about that?

620
00:41:55,650 --> 00:41:58,250
I've already agreed
to let Ju Ah resign.

621
00:41:58,620 --> 00:42:00,260
Yes, I'm sure.

622
00:42:01,190 --> 00:42:04,230
Ms. Gong seems to be doing just fine
since we broke up.

623
00:42:05,660 --> 00:42:06,900
It stings a little,

624
00:42:07,900 --> 00:42:09,130
but I suppose that's a good thing.

625
00:42:15,370 --> 00:42:16,940
Where were you? It's so late.

626
00:42:17,370 --> 00:42:19,280
I met with Director Yang.

627
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:21,880
Director Yang? Why?

628
00:42:22,610 --> 00:42:25,350
He said he can't keep his promise
to leave the company...

629
00:42:25,750 --> 00:42:27,350
and asked me to tell
your grandmother.

630
00:42:28,050 --> 00:42:30,050
Really? He decided not to leave?

631
00:42:31,690 --> 00:42:33,120
That's wonderful.

632
00:42:34,490 --> 00:42:36,130
You're not changing your mind,
are you?

633
00:42:37,060 --> 00:42:38,490
Of course not.

634
00:42:39,060 --> 00:42:42,160
I'm still quitting, so don't worry
and get some rest, okay?

635
00:42:42,600 --> 00:42:46,070
You saw the long faces on everyone
when we heard your results were bad.

636
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:48,100
So please, I'm begging you.

637
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:50,240
Go on inside
and get some rest, okay?

638
00:42:50,970 --> 00:42:52,270
You're sure you're okay with this?

639
00:42:52,640 --> 00:42:55,210
Of course. No problem.

640
00:43:31,710 --> 00:43:33,020
(Taehan Group)

641
00:43:37,890 --> 00:43:42,120
(Taehan Group)

642
00:43:42,190 --> 00:43:45,390
I heard you've decided
to stay with the company.

643
00:43:46,330 --> 00:43:48,400
Is that why you're
packing up your things?

644
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,740
Yes. I'll be in the Design Office
until my resignation is final.

645
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:56,670
Are we...

646
00:43:57,840 --> 00:43:59,410
really doing the right thing?

647
00:44:03,450 --> 00:44:04,450
Yes.

648
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:06,080
It is.

649
00:44:09,220 --> 00:44:10,220
Director Yang.

650
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:14,290
Could I ask you for one last favor?

651
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:16,330
Anything.

652
00:44:18,060 --> 00:44:20,930
Please protect
Taehan's Fashion Division.

653
00:44:28,700 --> 00:44:30,540
The paperwork has piled up,
Director Yang.

654
00:44:30,870 --> 00:44:32,370
Please take care of them
as soon as you can.

655
00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:34,840
Well, then.

656
00:44:47,960 --> 00:44:50,030
(Resignation Letter)

657
00:45:07,340 --> 00:45:09,680
An atelier, just for you.

658
00:45:10,180 --> 00:45:11,180
Gosh.

659
00:45:13,380 --> 00:45:14,520
Hey, take a look.

660
00:45:15,150 --> 00:45:17,120
- Oh.
- We have to maintain...

661
00:45:19,960 --> 00:45:20,990
Congratulations.

662
00:45:25,730 --> 00:45:27,030
I bet you can't.

663
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:31,700
- Come on in, Director Yang.
- Okay.

664
00:45:59,060 --> 00:46:02,930
What is this nonsense?
Withdrawing her resignation?

665
00:46:03,030 --> 00:46:04,030
Says who?

666
00:46:04,800 --> 00:46:06,400
Says me, Director Baek.

667
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:13,140
I sent Director Hong back.
I've reversed the transition.

668
00:46:14,010 --> 00:46:17,680
And it looked like he was tearing up
a little on his way out.

669
00:46:18,110 --> 00:46:21,150
Maybe you should go console him.
If you'll excuse me.

670
00:46:22,250 --> 00:46:24,490
Who's got your back,
making you act so bold?

671
00:46:25,150 --> 00:46:26,890
Hwangbo Hye Su?
She's just a figurehead.

672
00:46:27,290 --> 00:46:28,290
Or...

673
00:46:29,020 --> 00:46:30,930
the Chairman, who's on his deathbed?

674
00:46:36,530 --> 00:46:37,530
My backing?

675
00:46:38,170 --> 00:46:39,170
It's love.

676
00:46:51,210 --> 00:46:53,150
What is he, a lunatic?

677
00:46:54,050 --> 00:46:55,150
More importantly, Director Baek.

678
00:46:55,820 --> 00:46:56,820
Every weekend,

679
00:46:57,190 --> 00:46:59,450
a man has been visiting
the Chairman's hospital room.

680
00:47:01,790 --> 00:47:02,790
What?

681
00:47:04,360 --> 00:47:06,800
So they're really over for good?

682
00:47:07,300 --> 00:47:08,330
It looks that way.

683
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:10,930
Well, that's a silver lining,
I suppose.

684
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:12,770
At least we still have Pacu Nacho.

685
00:47:17,010 --> 00:47:19,510
His name is Park Jun Hyeok,
from the Fashion Division.

686
00:47:20,380 --> 00:47:21,780
Find out what
their relationship is...

687
00:47:22,440 --> 00:47:24,510
and what that bastard is after.

688
00:47:25,050 --> 00:47:26,050
Understood.

689
00:47:39,800 --> 00:47:41,930
(To Na Seon Hae)

690
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:50,710
- The owner's out. What now?
- It's fine.

691
00:47:51,140 --> 00:47:53,440
We can't just stay closed.
I'll figure something out.

692
00:47:54,010 --> 00:47:55,910
Okay, I'll let them know.

693
00:47:55,980 --> 00:47:59,080
Okay. I heard you met your mother?

694
00:47:59,450 --> 00:48:01,580
Yes.

695
00:48:02,020 --> 00:48:03,490
That's great. Congratulations.

696
00:48:03,950 --> 00:48:04,950
Thank you.

697
00:48:05,620 --> 00:48:09,560
Before I leave,
with the friends I made in Korea,

698
00:48:09,630 --> 00:48:13,130
I'd like to have one last meal here.
Can I make a reservation?

699
00:48:13,400 --> 00:48:17,300
- Of course. When are you leaving?
- After I finish my homework.

700
00:48:17,700 --> 00:48:19,840
I have two things left
to take care of.

701
00:48:21,500 --> 00:48:23,970
Eun Bin will be coming
to dinner too.

702
00:48:24,270 --> 00:48:25,270
What?

703
00:48:26,210 --> 00:48:27,280
Right...

704
00:48:28,010 --> 00:48:29,010
Okay.

705
00:48:29,310 --> 00:48:30,310
Okay, then.

706
00:48:37,420 --> 00:48:39,020
Come on. Open up.

707
00:48:41,190 --> 00:48:44,430
Auntie, please eat some porridge.
Okay?

708
00:48:44,530 --> 00:48:46,500
I even made it myself.

709
00:48:49,430 --> 00:48:51,170
You're as stubborn as a mule.

710
00:48:51,570 --> 00:48:53,770
You'll die too at this rate.
Don't you get it?

711
00:48:56,040 --> 00:48:57,210
This is driving me crazy.

712
00:48:58,510 --> 00:48:59,510
Haven't you ever heard the saying?

713
00:48:59,980 --> 00:49:02,410
The living have to go on living.
Right?

714
00:49:03,280 --> 00:49:04,280
Come on, open up.

715
00:49:09,420 --> 00:49:11,820
(Condolence Gift)

716
00:49:11,890 --> 00:49:15,160
(Dr. Yang Dong Ik)

717
00:49:30,070 --> 00:49:31,070
Eun Bin.

718
00:49:31,340 --> 00:49:33,980
Dad, you have to do something.

719
00:49:34,510 --> 00:49:37,380
Auntie could be in real trouble.

720
00:49:38,210 --> 00:49:40,550
All right, I know. I know, but...

721
00:49:42,320 --> 00:49:44,950
I just don't know
where to even start.

722
00:50:00,070 --> 00:50:01,070
Seong Mi.

723
00:50:01,840 --> 00:50:02,840
How are you holding up?

724
00:50:03,910 --> 00:50:04,910
I'm just...

725
00:50:05,640 --> 00:50:06,640
I don't know.

726
00:50:07,380 --> 00:50:11,080
I'm calling
as your doctor right now.

727
00:50:11,480 --> 00:50:13,120
If you want to talk about anything,
I'm listening.

728
00:50:14,250 --> 00:50:15,280
Talk?

729
00:50:16,790 --> 00:50:18,450
What could I possibly have to say?

730
00:50:20,590 --> 00:50:22,190
Do you just feel completely empty?

731
00:50:24,060 --> 00:50:25,060
Yes.

732
00:50:25,460 --> 00:50:27,400
That's normal
when you're overwhelmed.

733
00:50:28,530 --> 00:50:32,170
When a situation is unbearable,
you might shut down your emotions...

734
00:50:32,770 --> 00:50:35,600
and go into a state
of emotional numbness.

735
00:50:36,340 --> 00:50:39,880
I feel like I've lived
my entire life the wrong way.

736
00:50:42,640 --> 00:50:45,250
You see, all this time,
I thought I was the one abandoned.

737
00:50:46,250 --> 00:50:47,680
But now I know that wasn't true.

738
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:50,590
I was the one who abandoned her.

739
00:50:51,950 --> 00:50:55,690
You had no choice
but to be suspicious and guarded.

740
00:50:56,490 --> 00:51:00,760
That misunderstanding caused trauma,
leading to abandonment anxiety.

741
00:51:02,530 --> 00:51:04,130
Listen to me carefully,
Yang Dong Ik.

742
00:51:05,600 --> 00:51:06,840
It's not your fault.

743
00:51:07,740 --> 00:51:08,740
Really?

744
00:51:10,710 --> 00:51:12,170
It's really not my fault?

745
00:51:13,440 --> 00:51:14,510
Of course not.

746
00:51:15,440 --> 00:51:17,280
But I can't undo it.

747
00:51:18,880 --> 00:51:20,750
There's nothing I can do.

748
00:51:22,720 --> 00:51:26,460
All of your anxiety up to now
has stemmed from the past.

749
00:51:27,560 --> 00:51:28,560
That's right.

750
00:51:29,560 --> 00:51:32,490
But you still have
so many relationships in your life.

751
00:51:33,760 --> 00:51:35,700
And mending those relationships...

752
00:51:36,230 --> 00:51:39,870
will give you the strength
to heal and move forward.

753
00:51:41,940 --> 00:51:42,940
Thank you.

754
00:51:56,050 --> 00:51:59,420
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

755
00:52:06,700 --> 00:52:07,700
Here's your tea.

756
00:52:11,030 --> 00:52:13,070
Dae Han, have a seat.

757
00:52:16,370 --> 00:52:20,110
What are you doing at work already?
You should be resting.

758
00:52:22,610 --> 00:52:25,480
First, I want to say
I'm sorry to you both.

759
00:52:27,450 --> 00:52:29,250
And I'm truly grateful.

760
00:52:31,050 --> 00:52:32,650
For talking me into doing
"Human Theater."

761
00:52:34,620 --> 00:52:35,620
My mom...

762
00:52:37,230 --> 00:52:38,260
She got to see it all.

763
00:52:39,590 --> 00:52:41,200
How my family is doing,

764
00:52:42,500 --> 00:52:44,930
how well my kids grew up...

765
00:52:46,840 --> 00:52:48,370
She saw it all
before she passed away.

766
00:52:49,700 --> 00:52:52,840
We really did a good thing. Right?

767
00:52:54,740 --> 00:52:55,740
Thank you, really.

768
00:52:57,280 --> 00:52:59,010
Thank you for looking after my mom,

769
00:52:59,810 --> 00:53:02,350
and thank you so much
for seeing her off with me.

770
00:53:04,020 --> 00:53:05,520
I'll spend the rest of my life
making it up to you.

771
00:53:07,760 --> 00:53:10,690
Repay us for what? Forget about it.

772
00:53:11,190 --> 00:53:14,460
You just focus on
pulling yourself together, okay?

773
00:53:14,830 --> 00:53:15,830
He's right, you know.

774
00:53:16,700 --> 00:53:17,900
And take care of your family, too.

775
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:21,040
Hey...

776
00:53:21,640 --> 00:53:22,640
Dae Han.

777
00:53:23,410 --> 00:53:24,410
Yes?

778
00:53:37,020 --> 00:53:38,020
Dae Han?

779
00:53:43,120 --> 00:53:44,330
Dae Han...

780
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:47,800
Yes, it's me.

781
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:50,430
Are you going to keep
making me worry like this?

782
00:53:53,270 --> 00:53:54,270
It's so hard for you, isn't it?

783
00:53:55,900 --> 00:53:58,070
But Dong Suk,
if you fall apart like this,

784
00:53:59,540 --> 00:54:00,940
how can your mom rest in peace?

785
00:54:03,380 --> 00:54:05,880
Let's be strong. Okay?

786
00:54:06,350 --> 00:54:08,580
Let's be strong
and show her that we're living well.

787
00:54:21,830 --> 00:54:22,830
Don't cry.

788
00:54:44,650 --> 00:54:45,790
It's okay.

789
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:58,530
Even if it's the last thing I do,
I feel I have to apologize.

790
00:55:00,300 --> 00:55:02,400
Why would you say
something like that?

791
00:55:05,370 --> 00:55:06,570
It's my fault.

792
00:55:07,510 --> 00:55:09,210
Everything is my fault.

793
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:10,850
I...

794
00:55:12,610 --> 00:55:16,350
I believed the rumors
instead of my own wife.

795
00:55:17,920 --> 00:55:19,920
I should've been
her biggest supporter,

796
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:23,460
but I was the first one
to point the finger.

797
00:55:26,260 --> 00:55:28,930
I'm just as guilty.

798
00:55:33,870 --> 00:55:36,500
There's only one way...

799
00:55:37,170 --> 00:55:38,510
I can be forgiven for this.

800
00:55:42,380 --> 00:55:43,850
We have to find Gi Cheol.

801
00:55:46,980 --> 00:55:47,980
In every way possible,

802
00:55:48,350 --> 00:55:51,650
I'll do everything
in my power to find him.

803
00:55:52,750 --> 00:55:57,360
It's the last thing I can do
while I'm still alive.

804
00:56:14,780 --> 00:56:17,280
This is a letter
that In Ok left for you.

805
00:56:19,880 --> 00:56:20,880
What?

806
00:56:23,350 --> 00:56:24,350
Seon Hae.

807
00:56:25,120 --> 00:56:28,590
I'm sorry for leaving
without saying a word to you.

808
00:56:29,720 --> 00:56:33,960
I was always so envious
of your close-knit, happy family.

809
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:38,930
I hope your family is still close
and doing well.

810
00:57:01,990 --> 00:57:04,630
Why didn't I trust you?

811
00:57:04,990 --> 00:57:07,330
Why did I let myself get swayed
by the rumors?

812
00:57:08,260 --> 00:57:11,170
If I had trusted you
instead of the rumors...

813
00:57:11,630 --> 00:57:13,470
and started looking for you
right away...

814
00:57:18,340 --> 00:57:19,340
Here.

815
00:57:20,740 --> 00:57:21,740
Hey.

816
00:57:22,380 --> 00:57:25,380
- Not there.
- It's there. Why his side, Dad?

817
00:57:25,450 --> 00:57:26,450
Hey!

818
00:57:27,320 --> 00:57:30,550
- Hey, block him! You, be quiet!
- What?

819
00:57:30,720 --> 00:57:31,720
Come on.

820
00:57:31,790 --> 00:57:36,660
You'd still be running the clinic
with our sons today.

821
00:57:36,830 --> 00:57:40,160
- Dad, that's not fair.
- And you and I...

822
00:57:44,500 --> 00:57:46,570
would still be
cherishing each other...

823
00:57:47,140 --> 00:57:49,040
and living happily together,
wouldn't we?

824
00:57:54,180 --> 00:57:57,280
I know I can't turn back time,

825
00:57:57,980 --> 00:57:59,250
but for the days I have left,

826
00:57:59,780 --> 00:58:03,150
I'm determined to live them happily.

827
00:58:04,220 --> 00:58:05,420
That's why we...

828
00:58:05,920 --> 00:58:09,890
have resolved to find you,
no matter what.

829
00:58:17,300 --> 00:58:18,300
(Missing Person)

830
00:58:18,370 --> 00:58:19,830
(From Onjeong Market's
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,)

831
00:58:19,900 --> 00:58:21,340
(we are looking for
Dr. Gong Gi Cheol.)

832
00:58:24,240 --> 00:58:25,610
(It has been 30 years,)

833
00:58:25,670 --> 00:58:27,710
(but his family is still
waiting for their father.)

834
00:58:34,450 --> 00:58:35,680
He'll come back. I'm sure of it.

835
00:58:37,350 --> 00:58:38,350
Right.

836
00:58:42,160 --> 00:58:46,860
- We should've done this sooner.
- Yes.

837
00:58:46,930 --> 00:58:49,860
Hello. Thank you again
for coming to pay your respects.

838
00:58:49,930 --> 00:58:52,630
- Of course. I hope it went well.
- Thank you.

839
00:58:53,470 --> 00:58:55,870
Dr. Gong, could we speak
with you for a moment?

840
00:58:58,040 --> 00:58:59,110
Of course.

841
00:59:02,610 --> 00:59:06,250
Any news about my father?

842
00:59:06,950 --> 00:59:10,550
We checked with the police,
but on the unidentified bodies list,

843
00:59:10,620 --> 00:59:13,220
there were no matches
for your father.

844
00:59:13,660 --> 00:59:16,120
So, does that mean
he could still be alive?

845
00:59:16,620 --> 00:59:20,700
There's a good chance,
but his national ID has been voided,

846
00:59:21,130 --> 00:59:25,170
so we don't see any signs of life
from medical, phone, or bank data.

847
00:59:26,700 --> 00:59:29,340
But no matter how I look at it,

848
00:59:29,340 --> 00:59:31,140
my father had
no reason to run away...

849
00:59:31,510 --> 00:59:34,410
or to just not come back home.

850
00:59:35,210 --> 00:59:37,980
That's what I was getting at.
Is it possible that he...

851
00:59:38,780 --> 00:59:41,250
could have lost his memory?

852
00:59:42,280 --> 00:59:46,620
If he ended up at a police station,
wouldn't they have contacted us?

853
00:59:46,720 --> 00:59:48,860
(Police)

854
00:59:49,690 --> 00:59:51,430
What? Why?

855
00:59:51,960 --> 00:59:55,200
To be honest, we're also considering
the possibility of foul play.

856
00:59:56,460 --> 00:59:59,700
- Foul play?
- Yes. For example,

857
01:00:00,470 --> 01:00:01,900
a kidnapping, for instance.

858
01:00:02,400 --> 01:00:03,940
You mean...

859
01:00:04,670 --> 01:00:08,340
- that someone took my father?
- No.

860
01:00:08,640 --> 01:00:12,210
I'm just saying we should be open
to all possibilities.

861
01:00:14,780 --> 01:00:15,950
On that note,

862
01:00:16,250 --> 01:00:19,390
did he make any enemies
about 30 years ago?

863
01:00:20,120 --> 01:00:23,020
Or anything at all like that.

864
01:00:23,760 --> 01:00:25,490
Enemies?

865
01:00:26,630 --> 01:00:28,830
No, who on earth would...

866
01:00:46,610 --> 01:00:49,120
Honey.
I'm heading out for a little while.

867
01:01:38,030 --> 01:01:40,030
<i>You are my personal IV drip</i>

868
01:01:40,030 --> 01:01:42,570
<i>My very own intravenous shot</i>

869
01:01:43,040 --> 01:01:44,070
Jeong Han.

870
01:01:44,510 --> 01:01:46,770
Does your heart start racing
when you see Seong Mi?

871
01:01:47,280 --> 01:01:48,880
I bet it does.

872
01:01:48,940 --> 01:01:52,750
Dad, come on. This is my thing,
why are you butting in?

873
01:01:53,920 --> 01:01:56,750
Hey, let me see that.
Let me see. Good grief.

874
01:01:57,950 --> 01:01:59,220
Seriously.

875
01:01:59,220 --> 01:02:00,690
<i>Makes my heart pound</i>

876
01:02:00,690 --> 01:02:01,890
<i>It pounds</i>

877
01:02:01,960 --> 01:02:04,830
It's supposed to pound, right?
Thump thump?

878
01:02:06,190 --> 01:02:07,400
<i>You are my personal IV drip</i>

879
01:02:07,400 --> 01:02:09,000
<i>My very own intravenous shot</i>

880
01:02:09,660 --> 01:02:12,500
<i>You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>

881
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:16,070
- It has to make your heart pound.
- Faster?

882
01:02:21,740 --> 01:02:23,140
<i>You are my personal IV drip</i>

883
01:02:23,140 --> 01:02:25,150
<i>My very own intravenous shot</i>

884
01:02:25,610 --> 01:02:29,220
<i>You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>

885
01:02:29,620 --> 01:02:31,050
<i>You are my IV drip</i>

886
01:02:31,050 --> 01:02:33,350
<i>My personal Band-Aid</i>

887
01:02:33,750 --> 01:02:37,260
<i>You heal all my wounds</i>

888
01:02:43,700 --> 01:02:44,700
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

889
01:02:45,700 --> 01:02:47,700
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
"Human Theater")

890
01:03:13,460 --> 01:03:16,300
(Missing Person)

891
01:03:19,370 --> 01:03:22,270
(Recipe For Love)

892
01:03:23,070 --> 01:03:26,740
Do you know
who Hyun Bin has a crush on?

893
01:03:27,070 --> 01:03:28,080
No, I don't.

894
01:03:28,380 --> 01:03:29,410
I think you do.

895
01:03:30,080 --> 01:03:34,050
Are you saying she's a single mother
with a child born out of wedlock?

896
01:03:35,980 --> 01:03:37,820
Okay, perfect.

897
01:03:38,120 --> 01:03:41,260
I'm thinking I should
formally set the two of them up.

898
01:03:42,620 --> 01:03:46,790
If I give Dae Han my blessing,
don't you think Ju Ah will be upset?

899
01:03:46,960 --> 01:03:50,570
Is water really going to help?
You should have a real drink on ice.

900
01:03:51,000 --> 01:03:53,230
Even if I'm gone, take your medicine
when the alarm goes off.

901
01:03:53,630 --> 01:03:56,500
What if he's lost his memory?

902
01:03:56,700 --> 01:03:59,710
If he gets his memory back,
don't you think he might return?
